HEADWORD: Hotness
<hw>Hot"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The quality or state
of being hot.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Heat or excitement of mind or manner; violence;
vehemence; impetuosity; ardor; fury.</def> <rj><au>M.
Arnold.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

